SIMPLE: sulphacid
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sulphacid
<hw>Sulph*ac"id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Sulpho-</ets> + <ets>acid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An acid in which, to a greater or less extent, sulphur plays a part
analogous to that of oxygen in an oxyacid; thus, thiosulphuric and
sulpharsenic acids are <xex>sulphacids</xex>; -- called also
<altname>sulphoacid</altname>. See the Note under <er>Acid</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sulphamate</ent>⟦br⟧
